Subject: Re: [T2] Clutch ... (I Love you all ..)

> It's possible that the nut has "self adjusted" itself out .. what do the
> assembled think of loctite ?   I don't like the idea myself .. a little
> bit
> of rust would make it a little stiffer ..   Humm ..
>

If you have the correct nut, you shouldn't need loctite. The trick when
adjusting the clutch cable is to hold on to the cable end with vise grips
and then turn the nut. There are bumps on the wingnut that keep it from
loosening.


